prompt: What are the top 5 cities with most recalls?
sql: SELECT   t1.city,   COUNT(t1.recall_number) AS num_recalls FROM   `talk2data-genai-sa.fda_food.food_enforcement` AS t1 GROUP BY   1 ORDER BY   num_recalls DESC LIMIT   5

prompt: How are recalls across the months in 2023?  Use full month names
sql: SELECT   FORMAT_DATE('%B',recall_initiation_date) AS month,   COUNT(*) AS num_recalls FROM   `talk2data-genai-sa.fda_food.food_enforcement` WHERE   EXTRACT(YEAR   FROM     recall_initiation_date) = 2023 GROUP BY   1

prompt: How is the distribution across the classifications?
sql: SELECT   food_enforcement.classification,   COUNT(food_enforcement.event_id) AS num_events FROM   `talk2data-genai-sa.fda_food.food_enforcement` AS food_enforcement GROUP BY   1

prompt: What is the count of the workforce?
sql: SELECT workforce, count(*) as count_of_workforce FROM google_dei.dar_intersectional_hiring group by  workforce

prompt: What is the full movie name with top rating?
sql: SELECT max(R.AVERAGE_RATING) AS MAX_RATING, B.PRIMARY_TITLE FROM `talk2data-chat-with-sql-db.imdb.title_basics` AS B INNER JOIN `talk2data-chat-with-sql-db.imdb.title_ratings` AS R ON B.TCONST = R.TCONST GROUP BY B.PRIMARY_TITLE ORDER BY MAX_RATING DESC LIMIT 1;

prompt: Which person (with actual-name) has the highest number of movies?
sql: select n.primary_name, count(t.tconst) as movie_count from `talk2data-chat-with-sql-db.imdb.name_basics` n join `talk2data-chat-with-sql-db.imdb.title_principals` t on n.nconst = t.nconst group by n.primary_name order by movie_count desc limit 1;

prompt: Which person (with full name of one person) has directed the most number of movies?
sql: SELECT T1.PRIMARY_NAME FROM `talk2data-chat-with-sql-db.imdb.name_basics` AS T1 INNER JOIN `talk2data-chat-with-sql-db.imdb.title_crew` AS T2 ON T1.NCONST = T2.DIRECTORS ORDER BY DIRECTORS DESC LIMIT 1;

prompt: What movie(with actual name) has maximum number of votes?
sql: SELECT b.primary_title, a.num_votes FROM `talk2data-chat-with-sql-db.imdb.title_ratings` AS a JOIN `talk2data-chat-with-sql-db.imdb.title_basics` AS b ON a.tconst = b.tconst ORDER BY a.num_votes DESC LIMIT 1;

prompt: Find all actual movie name with a rating above 8.0
sql: SELECT n.PRIMARY_TITLE FROM `talk2data-chat-with-sql-db.imdb.title_basics` n WHERE n.TCONST IN( SELECT t.TCONST FROM `talk2data-chat-with-sql-db.imdb.title_ratings` t WHERE t.AVERAGE_RATING > 8.0 );

prompt: Which city had maximum number of sales?
sql: SELECT COUNT(SALES.ID_STORE), STORES.CITY_ID FROM RETAIL.SALES SALES JOIN RETAIL.STORES STORES ON SALES.ID_STORE = STORES.ID_STORE GROUP BY 2 ORDER BY COUNT(SALES.ID_STORE) DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: Which unique products share same parent hierarchy?
sql: select distinct T1.ID_PRODUCT from RETAIL.PRODUCTS AS T1 INNER JOIN RETAIL.PRODUCTS AS T2 ON T1.HIERARCHY1_ID = T2.HIERARCHY1_ID where T1.ID_PRODUCT <> T2.ID_PRODUCT

prompt: Which product (with product details) was sold with the maximum discount?
sql: select p.product_length, p.product_depth, p.product_width, p.cluster_id, p.hierarchy1_id, p.hierarchy2_id, p.hierarchy3_id, p.hierarchy4_id, p.hierarchy5_id, max(cast(s.promo_discount_2 as numeric)) as max_discount from retail.products as p join retail.sales as s on p.id_product = s.id_product group by p.product_length, p.product_depth, p.product_width, p.cluster_id, p.hierarchy1_id, p.hierarchy2_id, p.hierarchy3_id, p.hierarchy4_id, p.hierarchy5_id order by max_discount desc limit 1

prompt: Which city has maximum number of sales?
sql: select st.city_id, count(st.city_id) as city_sales_count from retail.sales as s join retail.stores as st on s.id_store = st.id_store group by st.city_id order by city_sales_count desc limit 1

prompt: Which product was sold most number of times?
sql: select p.id_product, count(p.id_product) as product_sales_count from retail.sales as s join retail.products as p on s.id_product = p.id_product group by p.id_product order by product_sales_count desc limit 1

prompt: Which city has maximum number of stores?
sql: select count(retail.stores.city_id), retail.stores.city_id from retail.stores group by 2 order by 1 desc limit 1
